Interview conducted by Howard Rheingold.

Video via http://blip.tv/howardrheingold/teaching-tech-savvy-kids-jessica-k-parker-interview-3757776

Jessica K. Parker is the author of the book, [[Teaching Tech-Savvy Kids]]: Bringing Digital Media into the Classroom, Grades 5-12. [http://teachingtechsavvykids.com/]


=Description=

"I talked with Jessica K. Parker earlier this month, and began our conversation with the three big questions she uses to frame the beginning and end of her book:

1.  What does learning look like in the 21st century? 

2.  What does literacy look like in the 21st century?

3.  What is knowledge in the 21st century? (Or what does it mean to  
know something in our mediated culture?)"
(http://dmlcentral.net/blog/howard-rheingold/its-learning-not-technology-jessica-k-parker)


